I"}<ol>
  <li>Roughly chop the basil, tomatoes and coat with oil and lemon juice.</li>
  <li>Crumble up the feta and mix with the basil and tomotoes. Sprinkle in rosemary.</li>
  <li>Cut a large pocket in the side of each chicken breast.</li>
  <li>Stuff your feta, basil, and tomato mixture into the pocket.</li>
  <li>Run a sheet of greaseproof paper under the tap for 5 seconds, then shake of the excess water and loosley scrunch it into a ball.</li>
  <li>Add the chicken breasts to a frying pan over a medium heat.</li>
  <li>Unscruch the greaseproof paper and lay it over the chicken, tucking it in at the edges to form a seal.</li>
  <li>Once browned on one side, flip the chicken and re-cover with the greaseproof paper.</li>
  <li>When nearly cooked put something heavy on top of the chicken (cast iron pan, brick etc.) to flatten it.</li>
  <li>Serve with whatever you like.</li>
</ol>
